The White House Office of the Press Secretary held a press conference call to preview President Obama's upcoming trip to Vietnam and Japan. The call included discussions on the objectives of the trip, such as strengthening partnerships, addressing security and strategic issues, promoting economic ties, and enhancing people-to-people exchanges. The officials also discussed the importance of the Asia-Pacific region to US national security and economic interests. In Vietnam, the President will engage in bilateral meetings, address issues like the Trans-Pacific Partnership (TPP), and speak to Vietnamese civil society. In Japan, the President will participate in the G7 Summit and visit Hiroshima. The officials also touched on topics like the Vietnam arms embargo, over-capacity in the steel industry, and the President's commitment to pursuing a world without nuclear weapons.